Bill B



Las Vegas, Nevada





Level 5  Contributor 


47 reviews 


15 hotel reviews





48 helpful votes 





“Only stay if you have to...previous reviews are right”


Reviewed June 22, 2014




The staff is rude here. They are just unhappy people. The Indian male in his 30's who is at the front desk most of the time better be glad his parents or grandparents own the place (I"m just assuming this) because he would have a hard time keeping a job at starbucks or anywhere there are customers. The location is really good. About a block away is an econolodge that I didn't stay but walked by and said to myself, 'I'd stay here at this econolodge when I come back'. I don't even know the prices of the econolodge but it's probably similar. Back to the Downtown Value Inn, the rooms on the 3rd floor are renovated and the corner room I stayed was actually nice. There are other rooms on the 2nd floor and one (room 29) in the basement that is deplorable. So beware when booking here and the safe thing to do is just find a place nearby so you can avoid the harsh personalities behind the desk of this hotel.


Room Tip: Get a room on the 3rd floor or stay somewhere else. Take a deep breath when dealing with the hotel...
See more room tips





Stayed June 2014, traveled solo



